      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.freebsd.org&#34;&gt;FreeBSD&lt;/a&gt; is an open source Unix-like operating system that can be
found (as a whole or in parts) in Apple macOS and iOS, Sony Playstation 4, Juniper routers
and NetApp storage filers, to name a few. It also powers services such as Netflix and WhatsApp.
I have been a developer with the project since 2003, and also contribute to related security-focused
projects such as &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.trustedbsd.org&#34;&gt;TrustedBSD&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/openbsm&#34;&gt;OpenBSM&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;commits&#34;&gt;Commits&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/freebsd/freebsd/commits?author=cbrueffer&#34;&gt;to the source code repository&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/freebsd/freebsd-doc/commits?author=cbrueffer&#34;&gt;to the documentation repository&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/freebsd/freebsd-ports/commits?author=cbrueffer&#34;&gt;to the ports repository&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
